<title>USA: Jean Philippe sees Q1 $1.3 mln charge.</title>
<headline>Jean Philippe sees Q1 $1.3 mln charge.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Jean Philippe Fragrances Inc said as part of a planned restructuring, the company would reduce its workforce and take a pre-tax charge of $1.3 million against first quarter earnings.</p>
<p>The company said as part of its agreement to sell the Cutex trademarks by Cheesebrough-Pond to Carson Inc, it entered into a pact to relinquish its Cutex nail and lip products license.  In connection with this deal, the company said all current inventory was to be bought and certain liabilities would be assumed by Carson.</p>
<p>&quot;Relinquishing the Cutex license is an integral part of a planned restructuring of our domestic operations,&quot; Chairman Jean Madar said.</p>
<p>He said: &quot;As a result we can now focus company resources on our profitable core altnerative designer fragrance business here in the United States and around the world.&quot;</p>
<p>The company did not specify the size of potential layoffs.</p>
